    ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                                    RNA Editing Standard Pipeline    

    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

An pipeline designed to run RNA editing analysis.

the pipeline input is sra accessions list or folder with fastq files

every .nf file have compatible .config file in the Configs folder

run the nf file with:

nextflow -c file.config run file.nf 

set your deserved genome by 
-profile like

for running the whole pipeline run:

nextflow -c /home/alu/twerski/Scripts/Nextflow/Levanon_lab_NEXTFLOW_PIPELINE/Configs/Docker/full_levanon_pipeline.nf.docker.config run /home/full_levanon_pipeline.nf -profile hg38 --use_existing_fastq false --ACC_list /home/alu/twerski/Scripts/Nextflow/training_data/small_srr.RL75.Human.txt --genome_length 75 --project_dir $PWD &> run.out.txt &


the pipeline consists of two major pipelines:
-  downloadAndPreprocess.nf
    will run quality checks and will clean the retrieved fastq files
-  analizeEditing_on_cleanData.nf
    will map fastq files using star, and calculate gene expression and RNA editing in several ways
you can run any of the two pipeline by itself or run the small subpipelines in the Subpipline folder

every nf file contain example of running command if you run its with --help


installation:

    install Nextflow and all its dependency https://nextflow.io/ 

    If you not run on levanon labs servers, you need to take care of the following:

            download/create all the following genomic files and set the following params:
            # genome fasta
            set params.genome_file
            # expression_file like "ucscHg38GTExGeneExpression.bed.gz"
            set params.expression_file 
            # star indexd genome
            set params.star_genome
            # refSeq genes file like ucscHg38RefSeqCurated.bed.gz
            set params.refseq_file
            # snps file like ucscHg38CommonGenomicSNPs150.bed.gz
            set params.snp_file
            # salmon transcripts index
            set params.transcripts_index
            # for salmon - like gencode_v32.transcriptToGeneID.tab
            set params.tx2id_geneMap 

        take care of code that not run inside dockers:
            You can disable the summarizing scripts with the params
            run_cmp_summarize = false
            run_salmon_summary = false
            run_star_summarize_script = false

            If you run the summarize scripts, you need python2.7 with the packeges:
            os
            argparse
            sys
            subprocess
            traceback
            
            set 'which_python_27' to your python interpreter
            
            You also need to have and R running with 'Rscript' command with the following libraries:
            argparse
            cowplot
            data.table
            dplyr
            ggplot2
            log4r
            purrr
            reshape2
            tibble
            tidyr
